main.java.de.bsi.tsesimulator.msg

Class LogMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.java.de.bsi.tsesimulator.msg.LogMessage
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SystemLogMessage, TransactionLogMessage

    public class LogMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    The generic log message consisting of the following:
    • version
    • certified datatype
    • serial number
    • algorithm
    • parameters
    • signature counter
    • log time
    • signature counter
    A detailed description of the purpose and possible value(s) of each of these parameters can be found in BSI TR-03151.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    dpottkaemper

        public void setAlgorithm(java.lang.String algorithm)
        Used by the ERSSpecificModule to set the algorithm OID of each log message. Since the log message does not know the algorithm oid without the ERSSpecificModule, the algorithm is not set in the constructors of log messages.
